<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id065d4618-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s4661"><num value="4661">§ 4661.</num><heading> Establishment</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Labor shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id065d4619-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s4661/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> hire and fix the compensation of up to 5 additional full-time officers or employees of the Department of Labor; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id065d461a-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s4661/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> detail or assign such officers or employees to the United States Embassy or a United States Consulate in Mexico to carry out the duties described in <ref href="/us/usc/t19/s4662">section 4662 of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id065d461b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/113/tVII/s721">Pub. L. 116–113, title VII, § 721</ref>, <date date="2020-01-29">Jan. 29, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/86">134 Stat. 86</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
